A period ot* six caesa and seven membra interlocked. d. Benedicite persequentibus vos3 benedicite, et nolite maledicere. Gaudere cum gaudentibus, flere cum fientibus: idipsum invicem sentientes. A period of two pairs of balanced membra, closed by a single membrum. e. Non alta sapientes, sed humilibus consentientes! A closing period of two balanced membra.

It would be difficult to find, in sacred literature. a specimen of oratory illustrating more perfectly the Temperate Style than the above extract from the Epistle to the Romans. A very high degree of art is employed in a very delicate and inconspicuous fashion. The passage is worthy of a great religious teacher, and unquestion- ably has the right to stand as a model or* sacred eloquenee.
